  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Cut the courgettes into 1-inch slices.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper, and paprika (if using).",
    "Add the courgette slices to the bowl and toss to coat.",
    "Transfer the courgettes to a baking sheet and roast for 20-25 minutes, or until tender and lightly browned.",
    "Sprinkle parmesan cheese over the courgettes and return to the oven for an additional 1-2 minutes.",
    "Remove from the oven and serve hot."
